msgid "Single sign-on with OpenID Connect"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/configuring_domain/01_managing_security/oidc.rst:4
msgid "Caution"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/configuring_domain/01_managing_security/oidc.rst:7
msgid ""
"The availability of this feature depends on the license of the Opendatasoft "
"domain."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/configuring_domain/01_managing_security/oidc.rst:11
msgid "Register your OpenID Connect provider on your domain"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/configuring_domain/01_managing_security/oidc.rst:13
msgid "Navigate to the signup page in the domain configuration interface."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/configuring_domain/01_managing_security/oidc.rst:15
msgid "Check \"Allow access for OpenID Connect users\""
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/configuring_domain/01_managing_security/oidc.rst:20
msgid ""
"Copy your provider discovery document in the \"OpenID Connect provider "
"information field\"."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/configuring_domain/01_managing_security/oidc.rst:22
msgid ""
"This document should be formatted in JSON and can usually be retrieved from "
"your provider endpoint. It must at least contain the following attributes:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/configuring_domain/01_managing_security/oidc.rst:25
msgid "``issuer``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/configuring_domain/01_managing_security/oidc.rst:26
msgid "``authorization_endpoint``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/configuring_domain/01_managing_security/oidc.rst:27
msgid "``userinfo_endpoint``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/configuring_domain/01_managing_security/oidc.rst:28
msgid "``end_session_endpoint``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/configuring_domain/01_managing_security/oidc.rst:29
msgid "``jwks_uri``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/configuring_domain/01_managing_security/oidc.rst:31
msgid ""
"If you would like to disable local user creation, making sure only existing "
"users can connect to the platform through OpenID Connect, check the "
"\"Disable local user provisioning\" checkbox."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/configuring_domain/01_managing_security/oidc.rst:33
msgid ""
"Input the application credentials associated with your Opendatasoft domain."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/configuring_domain/01_managing_security/oidc.rst:35
msgid ""
"As you have registered your Opendatasoft domain as an OpenID Connect client "
"on your provider, you should get a pair of credentials, namely ``Client ID``"
" and ``Client secret``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/configuring_domain/01_managing_security/oidc.rst:38
msgid ""
"These credentials are used to authenticate requests made by the Opendatasoft"
" plateform on the provider endpoint."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/configuring_domain/01_managing_security/oidc.rst:40
msgid ""
"Simply copy these credentials in the \"Client ID\" and \"Client secret\" "
"fields."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/configuring_domain/01_managing_security/oidc.rst:42
msgid ""
"If you would like to use JWT tokens to impersonate API calls on the "
"Opendatasoft platform, check the \"Enable direct authentication with JWT "
"bearer tokens\" checkbox."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/configuring_domain/01_managing_security/oidc.rst:44
msgid "List optional additional scopes"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/configuring_domain/01_managing_security/oidc.rst:46
msgid ""
"Scopes in OpenID Connect are used to define the set of information (claims) "
"an application would like to receive about a connected user. By default, "
"Opendatasoft uses the following scopes: openid, profile and email. These "
"scopes make it possible to authenticate a user and to retrieve their email, "
"first name and last name."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/configuring_domain/01_managing_security/oidc.rst:50
msgid ""
"You can use additional scopes to add claims as additional attributes in a "
"user's profile and use them in :doc:`datasets security filters "
"</configuring_domain/01_managing_security/portal>`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/configuring_domain/01_managing_security/oidc.rst:53
msgid "List optional additional claims"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/configuring_domain/01_managing_security/oidc.rst:55
msgid ""
"Claims are attributes that are collected during the authentication process "
"and that describe the user. By default, Opendatasoft only stores the `sub` "
"claim. It is possible to store additionnal claims in the user profile. These"
" claims can then be used in :doc:`datasets security filters "
"</configuring_domain/01_managing_security/portal>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/configuring_domain/01_managing_security/oidc.rst:59
msgid ""
"Input the URL on which the user can edit their user profile on the identity "
"provider. When set, a link to this URL will be shown to the user in their "
"user account page. If left blank, no URL will be shown to the user in their "
"account page."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/configuring_domain/01_managing_security/oidc.rst:61
msgid ""
"Customize the OpenID Connect login link text. If left blank, a localized "
"default message will be displayed."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/configuring_domain/01_managing_security/oidc.rst:65
msgid "Register your domain on your identity provider"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/configuring_domain/01_managing_security/oidc.rst:67
msgid ""
"The configuration of the identity provider is implementation-dependant, but "
"it usually consists into specifiying on the identity provider the value of "
"the redirection URI, which should be under the form ``https://<YOUR "
"DOMAIN>/oidc/authenticate``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/configuring_domain/01_managing_security/oidc.rst:70
msgid ""
"Some providers may support a preformated configuration document in JSON "
"format. This document can be downloaded from the following address: "
"``https://<YOUR DOMAIN>/oidc/client_info``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/configuring_domain/01_managing_security/oidc.rst:75
msgid "Single logout"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/configuring_domain/01_managing_security/oidc.rst:77
msgid ""
"The Opendatasoft platform supports single logout with OpenID Connect by "
"means of the draft protocol OpenID Connect Back-Channel Logout."
msgstr ""
